General Motors Corp's HughesAircraft Co subsidiary said it has been chosen by BritishSatellite Broadcasting to negotiate for a contract worth about300 mln dlrs to deliver two satellites for direct broadcasttelevision.    The company said the first of the satellites is scheduledto start up three channels of direct broadcast satellitetelevision by late 1989.    The company said the contract should be signed by June 30. Each satellite would be equipped with three 110-watt channels. Reuter&#3;